Script,OpenAndRebid
window.currentPBSScenario = 'OpenAndRebid';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Open_and_Rebid';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for OpenAndRebid');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'OpenAndRebid',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1[CDHS] +Pass +[1-5][CDHSN] .* Pass\n(P|[1-5])
*/
# curate: kind=bidding
# convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
# convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge


dealer south

### Imported Leveling Code ###
c1 = hascard(west,2C)
c2 = hascard(east,2D)
c3 = hascard(west,3C)
c4 = hascard(east,3D)

keep06 = c1 and c2          // this is used later w/c3 & c4 expressions
keep44 = c3 or c4           // this is used later w/c1 & c2 expressions

keep015 = keep06 and c3
keep03 = keep06 and keep44
keep045 = keep06 and not c3
####06 = c1 and c2
keep11 = c1 and keep44
keep14 = c1 and not keep44
keep19 = c1 and not c2
keep25 = c1
keep30 = keep06 or c3
keep33 = c1 or (c2 and keep44)
####44 = c3 or c4
keep47 = keep44 or keep06

keep53 = not keep47
keep56 = not keep44
keep67 = not keep33
keep70 = not keep30
keep75 = not keep25
keep81 = not keep19
keep86 = not keep14
keep89 = not keep11
keep94 = not keep06
keep955 = not keep045
keep97 = not keep03
keep985 = not keep015
keep   = 1
keep0  = 0
### End of Imported Leveling Code ###
##### Imported Script: Define Calm Opponents #####

# Avoid concentration of values
cce = top4(east,clubs)<2
cde = top4(east,diamonds)<2
che = top4(east,hearts)<2
cse = top4(east,spades)<2
noConEast = cce and cde and che and cse

ccw = top4(west,clubs)<2
cdw = top4(west,diamonds)<2
chw = top4(west,hearts)<2
csw = top4(west,spades)<2
noConWest = ccw and cdw and chw and csw

balEast    = shape(east,any 4432 +any 4333)
unbalEast  = shape(east,xxxx -any 4432 -any 4333 -any 9xxx -any 8xxx -any 7xxx-any 6xxx -any 55xx)

balWest    = shape(west,any 4432 +any 4333)
unbalWest  = shape(west,xxxx -any 4432 -any 4333 -any 9xxx -any 8xxx -any 7xxx-any 6xxx -any 55xx)

calmEast = (unbalEast and noConEast and hcp(east)<8) or (balEast and hcp(east)<11)
calmWest = (unbalWest and noConWest and hcp(west)<8) or (balWest and hcp(west)<11)
calmOpps = calmEast and calmWest

##### End of Imported Script: Define Calm Opponents #####
# provides calmOpps (both opponents too weak/flat to interfere)

# ---- South's hand TYPE is the whole lesson: what is my prepared rebid? ----
sHcp = hcp(south)

# Balanced = 4333, 4432, or 5332 (a 5-card suit may be a major)
balanced = shape(south, any 4333 + any 4432 + any 5332)

# Bucket 1  Balanced 12-14  ->  open your suit, rebid 1NT   (e.g. 1H-1S-1NT)
balMin = balanced and sHcp > 11 and sHcp < 15

# Bucket 2  Balanced 18-19  ->  open your suit, jump to 2NT (e.g. 1C-1H-2NT)
balBig = balanced and sHcp > 17 and sHcp < 20

# Bucket 3  Unbalanced -> open your longest suit, rebid the second-longest.
#   A singleton or void, plus a 5+ card suit (major or minor) to open and rebid around.
longSuit = spades(south) > 4 or hearts(south) > 4 or diamonds(south) > 4 or clubs(south) > 4
hasShort = spades(south) < 2 or hearts(south) < 2 or diamonds(south) < 2 or clubs(south) < 2
unbal = longSuit and hasShort and sHcp > 11 and sHcp < 19

southHand = balMin or balBig or unbal

# ---- Responder: 6-11 HCP so partner responds and South gets to rebid ----
northHand = hcp(north) > 5 and hcp(north) < 12

# ---- Keep combined N/S below slam range so the auction stays in game/partscore ----
nsBelowSlam = hcp(north) + hcp(south) < 31

# ---- Calm opponents keep the focus on opener's rebid (no interference) ----

# ---- Level the three hand-type buckets so each shows up (18-19 is rare, keep it all) ----
levBalMin = balMin and keep67
levBalBig = balBig and keep
levUnbal  = unbal  and keep47
levelTheDeal = levBalMin or levBalBig or levUnbal

southHand and northHand and nsBelowSlam and calmOpps and levelTheDeal

action printoneline,
average "South HCP avg      " hcp(south),
average "Bal 12-14 (reb 1N) " 100 * balMin,
average "Bal 18-19 (reb 2N) " 100 * balBig,
average "Unbalanced (2nd)   " 100 * unbal,
average "Opens 1H/1S (5+ M) " 100 * (spades(south) > 4 or hearts(south) > 4),
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Basic Open & Rebid,\n\
--- Basic: Plan Your Rebid，Then Open (beginner)\n\
The habit this set builds: before you pick an opening bid，decide what you will REBID.\n\
That plan is what makes the auction easy -- and it can even decide which suit you open.\n\
Plan your rebid first，then open.\n\
\n\
Ask "what is my hand TYPE?"\n\
• Balanced (4333，4432，or 5332 -- no singleton or void，at most one doubleton)\n\
  Plan a notrump rebid that shows the balanced shape and your point range:\n\
  • 12-14 HCP: open your suit，plan to rebid 1NT      (e.g. 1!H-1!S-1NT)\n\
  • 18-19 HCP: open your suit，plan to jump to 2NT     (e.g. 1!C-1!H-2NT)\n\
  (15-17 balanced opens 1NT and is not in this set.)\n\
• Unbalanced (a singleton or void，with a long suit or two)\n\
  Plan to rebid your second suit -- then open the suit that makes that rebid easy.\n\
  With two long suits，open the HIGHER-ranking one so the second bid is cheap and does\n\
  not reverse: 1!S then 2!H (spades + hearts)，or 1!D then 2!C (both minors).\n\
  Planning first can even change what you open: with 5 clubs and 4 diamonds，open 1!D\n\
  so your 2!C rebid is comfortable -- open 1!C and partner's 1!S leaves you no good rebid.\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.advinbridge.com/this-week-in-bridge/637\n\
%OpenAndRebid%
